# UI Templates

- Follow root **`.editorconfig`** for web file formatting (indent, line length, EOL). See **`ui-editorconfig.mdc`** for a short summary and globs.
- Use Thymeleaf templates for UI screens and reusable server-rendered partials.
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling; avoid inline styles except for trivial one-off values.
- Use HTMX for dynamic updates such as partial refreshes, polling, sorting, filtering, and actions.
- Do not put business logic, status mapping, or data shaping in templates.
- Extract repeated markup into reusable Thymeleaf fragments instead of duplicating HTML blocks.
- Every screen should keep a clear hierarchy with `header`, `main content`, and `actions`.
- Tables must support filtering and sorting in the rendered UI.
- Use consistent status colors: `SUCCESS` green, `FAILED` red, `RUNNING` blue, `QUEUED` gray.
- Logs must be rendered in a monospaced, scrollable container.
- Make validation and error states visible near the top of the screen instead of burying them deep in the page.

```html
<main class="space-y-4">
  <div th:replace="~{fragments/actions :: toolbar(...)}"></div>
  <section hx-get="/jobs" hx-target="#job-table" hx-trigger="load, every 10s">
    <div th:replace="~{fragments/job-table :: table(${page})}"></div>
  </section>
</main>
```
